HB 746 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Owen
Abstract: Prohibits the requirement of any special permits outside of the permits issued by
the Department of Transportation and Development.
Present law requires oversized vehicles or combination of vehicles that do not meet the
requirements of present law obtain a special permit when using public highways of the state.
Further specifies that the Dept. of Transportation and Development (DOTD) be the entity
to issue special permits. Further authorizes any other agencies or departments of the state
or political subdivisions to issue other special permits.
Proposed law prohibits any special permit outside of the permits required by the DOTD.
Proposed law establishes a one-year moratorium on the issuance of local permits for
oversized vehicles and prohibits political subdivisions from adopting new permit
requirements during the established moratorium.
Effective upon the signature of governor or lapse of time for gubernatorial action.
(Amends R.S. 32:387(A))
