Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on Transportation,
Highways and Public Works to the original bill:
1. Make technical changes
2. Delete a provision that prohibited political subdivisions from adopting any
special permit that exceeded the requirements of state law.
3. Add provision to establish a one-year moratorium on the issuance of local
permits for oversized vehicles and prohibit political subdivisions from adopting
new permit requirements during the established moratorium.
4. Make proposed law effective upon signature of the governor or the lapse of time
for gubernatorial action.
The House Floor Amendments to the engrossed bill:
1. Make technical changes.
2. Provide for an exception applicable to Bossier Parish from the prohibition
against any special permits outside of that which is required by the Department
of Transportation and Development.
3. Add a provision establishing a one-year moratorium on the issuance of local
permits for oversized vehicles and prohibiting political subdivisions from
adopting new permit requirements during the moratorium.
